 {"id":"frankenpandas-ppry","title":"fd90.39: SqlInspector::has_column / column ergonomic helpers","description":"Extend fd90.38's SqlInspector with two ergonomic helpers matching SQLAlchemy.Inspector. has_column(table, column, schema) -> Result<bool> returns true when the column exists in the introspected table. column(table, column, schema) -> Result<Option<SqlColumnSchema>> returns the specific column's metadata bundle (declared_type, nullable, default_value, primary_key_ordinal, comment, autoincrement). Both delegate to columns(table, schema) and filter by name. Out-of-the-box semantics: missing table -> Ok(false) / Ok(None); missing column on existing table -> Ok(false) / Ok(None). Pure-delegation slice — no new behavior on the trait. Tests cover existing column, missing column on existing table, missing table, multi-schema routing.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"cc-pandas-2","created_at":"2026-04-25T22:05:41.586751274Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T22:09:06.967189025Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T22:09:06.964706967Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["fd90","review","sql"]}
